On Sun, 12 Jul 2009, Darren Evans-Young wrote:

> Trying to remove the clutch fork in the bell housing.
> I've moved the circlip over next to left fork.
> There is a plastic bushing in the case where the lever
> attaches. How does this bushing come out? It's being
> stubborn. I dont want to force it if there is something
> holding it in place.

There is a setscrew through the case and into that bushing.  remove the 
setscrew, then slide the bushing sideways off the shaft.  It can be 
stubborn.
